oads/sites/3/2019/09/mugabe-signs1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/mugabe-signs1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Prime Minister signing the freedom roll after he was made a Freeman of the City of Bulawayo. Standing behind the PRime Minister is the mayor of Bulawayo, Clr Nick Mabodoko (Pic taken on 23 July 1986) <img class="wp-image-466273 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/mugabe-family.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/mugabe-family.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/mugabe-family-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mugabe speaking with some of his relatives Mr Lewis Chandafira and Mrs Hilda Tshuma, in Mpopoma, Bulawayo (Pic taken on 19 August 1998) 